# Project Structure

- This is a project-specific rule file. It defines where code lives in this repository based on its current architectural state.
- This project is a **monorepo** managed via npm workspaces. All TypeScript source code lives inside packages under `packages/` and is compiled to `dist/` or `out/` within each package.
- The Domain Data7, Tests/Quality, Governance/Git, and Security/Performance rules remain integral and must be respected alongside this structure.

## Monorepo Layout

- `packages/data7-core/` — The core language kernel, compiler, transpiler, syntax parser, AST, semantics, analyzer, builder, and language services. It is environment-agnostic and reusable.
- `packages/data7-cli/` — The Command Line Interface wrapper around the core. Handles standard I/O for standalone compilations.
- `packages/data7-vscode/` — The VS Code extension. Contains VS Code UI adapters, providers, tree views, commands, and workspace integration. It imports `@data7/core`.

## Core Package (`packages/data7-core/src/`)

- `project/parser/` and `project/ast/`: The core syntax definitions and parsers.
- `project/generics/` and `project/sugars/`: Implement pure transformations over the AST and canonical code. Every sugar lives in `sugars/plugins/<sugar-id>/`.
- `analysis/` — Semantic reading, workspace indexing, type resolution, control flow, and dependency discovery.
- `diagnostics/` — Diagnostic codes, severity definitions, and AST-driven diagnostic assembly.
- `system-library/` — Native Data7 symbol catalog.
- `mcp/` — Isolated MCP adapter that reuses the existing runtime via shims.
- `infra/` — Configuration, constants, and logging.
- `utils/` — Pure domain-agnostic helpers.

## VS Code Package (`packages/data7-vscode/src/`)

- `providers/` — VS Code UI adapters. Providers consume AST/context/indexer from core.
- `services/` — Command implementations, VS Code integration, workspace trust, and IO orchestration.

## Files outside `src/`

- `AGENTS.md` — Mandatory implementation contract for AI agents. Keep it synchronized with the architecture rules and `project_context.md`.

- `docs/example/` — Canonical documentation fixtures. Headers and `_expected` output must reflect the current transpiler/linter before tests run; regenerate its README index from headers.
- `docs/linguagem-basic/` — Current language and tooling reference; do not describe removed feature flags or superseded pipelines.
- `docs/system-library/` — Generated human reference for `src/system-library/`.
- `docs/rfcs/` — Historical architecture decisions. Mark assumptions absent from this checkout as historical rather than operational.
